%N A068928 Number of incongruent ways to tile a 3 X 2n room with 1x2 Tatami mats. At most 3 Tatami mats may meet at a point.
%H A068928 Paolo Xausa, <a href="/A068928/b068928.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..1000</a>
%H A068928 R. J. Mathar, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/1311.6135">Paving rectangular regions with rectangular tiles,....</a>, arXiv:1311.6135 [math.CO], Table 10.
%H A068928 <a href="/index/Rec#order_06">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (1,2,-1,0,-1,-1).
%F A068928 For n >= 8, a(n) = a(n-1) + 2*a(n-2) - a(n-3) - a(n-5) - a(n-6).
%F A068928 From _R. J. Mathar_, Aug 30 2008: (Start)
%F A068928 O.g.f.: x*(2-4*x^2-x^4+x^6)/((1-x-x^2)*(1-x^2-x^4)).
%F A068928 a(n) = (A000045(n+1)+A053602(n+1))/2, n>1. (End)
%t A068928 LinearRecurrence[{1, 2, -1, 0, -1, -1}, {2, 2, 2, 4, 5, 9, 12}, 50] (* _Paolo Xausa_, May 25 2026 *)
